# 🚀 Lite-Server — Feature Suggestions

After a deep analysis of the codebase, here are feature suggestions prioritized by impact. They are grouped into **high-value quick wins**, **core platform features**, and **advanced capabilities**.

---

## 🏆 Tier 1 — High-Impact, High-Value

### 1. 🔗 Public Share Links (File & Folder Sharing)
**Who benefits:** Admin + Users
**Why it matters:** The `shares` table and `ShareSchema` already exist in your DB and types but are **completely unimplemented**. This is the single highest-value feature you can add.

**What it does:**
- Right-click a file/folder → "Create Share Link"
- Generates a unique public URL (e.g., `/s/abc123`) accessible **without login**
- Optional: password-protect the link, set expiry date, set max download count
- Admin dashboard to see all active share links and revoke them
- Download counter shown in the share management panel

> [!TIP]
> The database schema, Zod types, and token indexing are already in place — this is mostly API route + UI work.

---

### 2. 📂 Create New Folder (from UI)
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** The VFS has `mkdir()` but there's **no API route or UI** to create folders. Users must upload files into a path to implicitly create directories.

**What it does:**
- "New Folder" button in the file explorer toolbar
- Modal to name the folder → calls `POST /api/files/mkdir`
- Immediately navigates into the new folder

---

### 3. ✏️ Rename Files & Folders
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** The VFS has `rename()` but there's **no API route or UI**. Users must delete and re-upload to rename.

**What it does:**
- Right-click or inline-edit a file/folder name
- Calls `POST /api/files/rename` with `{ oldPath, newPath }`
- Instant UI update without full refresh

---

### 4. 📋 Move / Copy Files (Cut & Paste)
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** VFS has `rename()` (move) and `copy()` but **no API or UI**. File organization is impossible.

**What it does:**
- Select files → "Cut" or "Copy" action in toolbar
- Navigate to destination → "Paste" button appears
- Calls `POST /api/files/move` or `POST /api/files/copy`
- Supports multi-file operations

---

### 5. 🔍 Search / Filter Files
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** No way to find files across directories. As storage grows, this becomes critical.

**What it does:**
- Search bar in the toolbar — filters current directory in real-time
- Server-side recursive search (`GET /api/files/search?q=report&path=/uploads`)
- Results show full path with click-to-navigate

---

## 🏅 Tier 2 — Core Platform Features

### 6. 📊 Real Audit Log Viewer (Admin)
**Who benefits:** Admin
**Why it matters:** Audit logging infrastructure exists (`audit_logs` table, `logAudit()` method) but **no events are recorded and no UI exists** to view them.

**What it does:**
- Actually log events: login, upload, download, delete, share, user management
- Admin Console → new "Audit Logs" tab
- Filterable table: by user, action type, date range
- Export audit logs as CSV

---

### 7. 📈 Real Storage Analytics Dashboard (Admin)
**Who benefits:** Admin
**Why it matters:** The `/metrics` endpoint returns **hardcoded zeros**. The admin dashboard shows a static "15%" progress bar.

**What it does:**
- Real disk usage tracking: total, used, available (from `os.statvfs` or `df`)
- Upload/download byte counters (track in DB or memory)
- Per-user storage usage breakdown
- Storage trend chart (daily/weekly)
- File type distribution pie chart (images, videos, docs, archives)

---

### 8. 🔔 Toast Notifications System
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** All feedback currently uses `alert()` / `confirm()` / `prompt()` — blocking and ugly. This is a UX quality issue.

**What it does:**
- Replace all `alert()` calls with non-blocking toast notifications
- Success (green), error (red), warning (yellow), info (blue) variants
- Auto-dismiss with progress bar
- Stack multiple notifications

---

### 9. 📤 Upload Progress Bar with Cancellation
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** File uploads show no progress. Large files (up to 15GB configured) leave users guessing.

**What it does:**
- Real-time progress bar per file (using `XMLHttpRequest` or `fetch` with `ReadableStream`)
- Overall progress for multi-file uploads
- Cancel button per upload
- Resume failed uploads (chunked upload protocol — types already exist: `UploadChunkSchema`, `UploadSessionSchema`)

---

### 10. 🏷️ Per-User Storage Quotas (Admin)
**Who benefits:** Admin
**Why it matters:** No way to limit how much storage a user consumes. One user could fill the disk.

**What it does:**
- Admin sets quota per user (e.g., 5GB)
- Upload API checks quota before accepting
- Dashboard shows each user's usage vs. quota
- Warning when approaching limit (80%, 90%, 100%)

---

## 🥉 Tier 3 — Advanced Capabilities

### 11. 🔐 Per-Folder Access Control (ACL)
**Who benefits:** Admin
**Why it matters:** The `access_levels` table and `AccessLevelSchema` exist but are **completely unimplemented**. Currently all authenticated users see everything.

**What it does:**
- Admin assigns permissions per folder per user/group: `read`, `write`, `delete`, `share`
- VFS operations check ACLs before proceeding
- UI hides/disables actions the user doesn't have permission for
- Uses the existing `groups` table for group-based access

---

### 12. 👥 Group Management (Admin)
**Who benefits:** Admin
**Why it matters:** The `groups` and `user_groups` tables exist but are **unimplemented**. Groups are essential for ACL above.

**What it does:**
- Admin Console → "Groups" tab
- Create/delete groups, add/remove users
- Assign folder permissions to groups instead of individual users
- Bulk user management

---

### 13. 🗑️ Trash / Recycle Bin
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** Delete is permanent and immediate. Accidental deletion is a real data-loss risk.

**What it does:**
- Delete moves files to a `.trash/` virtual path instead of permanent removal
- "Trash" sidebar item shows deleted files with restore/permanent-delete options
- Auto-purge after configurable retention (e.g., 30 days)
- Admin can empty all users' trash

---

### 14. 📱 Responsive Mobile Layout
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** The current CSS layout assumes desktop. Mobile users get a poor experience.

**What it does:**
- Collapsible sidebar on mobile
- Touch-friendly file grid with swipe actions
- Bottom navigation bar on small screens
- Upload via mobile camera/gallery

---

### 15. 🌙 Theme Toggle (Dark / Light / System)
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** Currently hardcoded dark theme. Some users prefer light mode.

**What it does:**
- Toggle in navbar: Dark / Light / System preference
- Persisted in localStorage
- CSS variables already used — just swap the palette

---


### 16. 📝 Text File Editor (In-Browser)
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** Currently you can preview text files but can't edit them. Useful for config files, notes, markdown.

**What it does:**
- Click text files → opens in a code editor (Monaco or CodeMirror)
- Save button writes back via `PUT /api/files/content`
- Syntax highlighting for common file types
- Markdown preview mode

---

### 17. 🖼️ Image Thumbnail Generation
**Who benefits:** All users
**Why it matters:** Grid view shows emoji icons. Actual image thumbnails make the file browser much more useful.

**What it does:**
- Server generates thumbnails on upload (using `sharp`)
- Grid view shows actual image previews
- Lazy-loaded for performance
- Cached in a `.thumbnails/` directory

---

